We use the view ManageVersions.jspa to present a project's iteration plan.

Since this page is only accessible by project administrators, as a workaround we currently save this page as HTML file (including the pictures etc) and publish this HTML in our intranet. (See the attached ZIP file for an example).

I would appreciate a read-only representation of this ManageVersions.jspa for all our JIRA users, without the several add, edit, delete etc. buttons and links. Then we could link to this page directly from our intranet, and there were no redundancies between database and HTML representation.

